The paper deals with fingerprinting games, which involve coding and information theory concepts. The paper discusses capacity formulas and randomized fingerprinting schemes, which are typical topics in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of randomized sequences and decoding algorithms also suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses tradeoffs and bounds on various parameters, which is a common theme in optimization and learning theory (cs.LG).
